#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:1
msgid ""
"Get a connection from the pool and perform an HTTP request. This is the "
"lowest level call for making a request, so you'll need to specify all the "
"raw details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:7
msgid ""
"More commonly, it's appropriate to use a convenience method provided by :"
"class:`.RequestMethods`, such as :meth:`request`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:12
msgid ""
"`release_conn` will only behave as expected if `preload_content=False` "
"because we want to make `preload_content=False` the default behaviour "
"someday soon without breaking backwards compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/contrib/ntlmpool.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:17
msgid "HTTP request method (such as GET, POST, PUT, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:20
msgid "The URL to perform the request on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:23
msgid ""
"Data to send in the request body, either :class:`str`, :class:`bytes`, an "
"iterable of :class:`str`/:class:`bytes`, or a file-like object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:27
msgid ""
"Dictionary of custom headers to send, such as User-Agent, If-None-Match, "
"etc. If None, pool headers are used. If provided, these headers completely "
"replace any pool-specific headers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:32
msgid ""
"Configure the number of retries to allow before raising a :class:`~urllib3."
"exceptions.MaxRetryError` exception.  Pass ``None`` to retry until you "
"receive a response. Pass a :class:`~urllib3.util.retry.Retry` object for "
"fine-grained control over different types of retries. Pass an integer number "
"to retry connection errors that many times, but no other types of errors. "
"Pass zero to never retry.  If ``False``, then retries are disabled and any "
"exception is raised immediately. Also, instead of raising a MaxRetryError on "
"redirects, the redirect response will be returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:33
msgid ""
"Configure the number of retries to allow before raising a :class:`~urllib3."
"exceptions.MaxRetryError` exception."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:36
msgid ""
"Pass ``None`` to retry until you receive a response. Pass a :class:`~urllib3."
"util.retry.Retry` object for fine-grained control over different types of "
"retries. Pass an integer number to retry connection errors that many times, "
"but no other types of errors. Pass zero to never retry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:42
msgid ""
"If ``False``, then retries are disabled and any exception is raised "
"immediately. Also, instead of raising a MaxRetryError on redirects, the "
"redirect response will be returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:48
msgid ""
"If True, automatically handle redirects (status codes 301, 302, 303, 307, "
"308). Each redirect counts as a retry. Disabling retries will disable "
"redirect, too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:53
msgid ""
"If ``True``, will make sure that the host of the pool requests is consistent "
"else will raise HostChangedError. When ``False``, you can use the pool on an "
"HTTP proxy and request foreign hosts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:58
msgid ""
"If specified, overrides the default timeout for this one request. It may be "
"a float (in seconds) or an instance of :class:`urllib3.util.Timeout`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:63
msgid ""
"If set and the pool is set to block=True, then this method will block for "
"``pool_timeout`` seconds and raise EmptyPoolError if no connection is "
"available within the time period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:68
msgid ""
"If False, then the urlopen call will not release the connection back into "
"the pool once a response is received (but will release if you read the "
"entire contents of the response such as when `preload_content=True`). This "
"is useful if you're not preloading the response's content immediately. You "
"will need to call ``r.release_conn()`` on the response ``r`` to return the "
"connection back into the pool. If None, it takes the value of ``response_kw."
"get('preload_content', True)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:78
msgid ""
"If True, urllib3 will send the body using chunked transfer encoding. "
"Otherwise, urllib3 will send the body using the standard content-length "
"form. Defaults to False."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:83
msgid ""
"Position to seek to in file-like body in the event of a retry or redirect. "
"Typically this won't need to be set because urllib3 will auto-populate the "
"value when needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/contrib/ntlmpool.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool.NTLMConnectionPool.urlopen:88
msgid ""
"Additional parameters are passed to :meth:`urllib3.response.HTTPResponse."
"from_httplib`"
msgstr ""
